unning threads is lower than the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"maximal allowed number of threads, a new thread is started (or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reused) with the properties given to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_pool_new()"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Otherwise, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":" stays in the queue until a thread in this pool"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"finishes its previous task and processes ","type":"text"},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" can be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" to ignore errors, or non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to report","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"errors. An error can only occur when a new thread couldn’t be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"created. In that case "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"text":" is simply appended to the queue of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work to do."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before version 2.32, this function did not return a success status."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadpoolref\/push(data:)"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPoolRef/ThreadPoolProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"ThreadPoolProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpoolref\/threadpoolprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef\/ThreadPoolProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib